The paper focuses on designing complex neural architectures for vision applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks (DNNs) and Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) for architecture search suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of MCTS for search and optimization also suggests that it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of improving a variety of vision applications suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
